data.title: Sushi in Milwaukee
data.text: Came early and Chef James greet me and welcome me to the restaurant. I was the first one of the day. I order the double tuna roll. Amazing. Fish was very tender and fresh.  James tiene he has been chef for 27 years and recently moved form California. Good for the east coast!

data.title: Come for the happy hour deals!
data.text: My husband works a few minutes away and this has been one of our most visited restaurants in Milwaukee. The deals for happy hour are great, we order several small plates, drinks and some rolls for a good price. The atmosphere is calm, fun and relaxing. We have taken many out of town guests here when we find out they like Sushi. The waiters/waitresses' are always very friendly and treat us like friends. We will continue coming here as long as its open!

data.title: Solid sushi, great service
data.text: Travel irregularities left me stranded in downtown Milwaukee for an unplanned stay, so I looked for a quick place to grab a good meal and found Sake Tumi near my hotel.  The meal I got was very, very good - Chirashi served in a large bowl.  The serving size was more than adequate, and the selection of micro-brews and premium sake was outstanding for a restaurant of this type.  Service at the bar was attentive and friendly - as good as it gets.  Next time I'm in MKE, I'll go back and take friends.

data.title: Great sushi and Asian food!
data.text: Ordered take-out while I was staying at the Pfister around the corner. Food was delicious and lunch prices were great.

data.title: Loft type atmosphere with great food
data.text:
I recently ate at Sake Tumi and had 4 different Maki. Each one was better than the next.  The quality and taste is excellent and the quantity/size is very good.  They serve fabulous Miso soup.

The service was a bit rushed (at least to take our order) but was good for drink refills.  

The seating is pretty close.  It is difficult to have a private conversation due to the proximity of others.

data.title: First Time Was A Charm
data.text: My first experience with sushi  was awesome! The staff was eager to assist me on my adventure. The food was great and venue is beautifully decorated. They serve both Japanese and Korean selections. I ate a lot and I learned a lot about sushi. I can't wait to go back with my friends and family.

data.title: Great Sushi!
data.text: The Godzilla is mine and my boyfriends absolute favorite. Service is always great as well. It is a bit pricey in comparison to other sushi places in the area, so go on Sunday's when it is half off.

data.title: Best sushi in Milwaukee!
data.text: Grade A quality sushi and excellent service! Unique atmosphere with a New York look to it. Definitely recommended for a date night!

data.title: Just So-So
data.text:
Visited recently for dinner with a couple friends. We had gift cards so we thought we would try it. First, parking is difficult even on a quiet weeknight so the discounted parking at the structure just a block away is a nice option. When we entered we were greeted and seated promptly. Cool atmosphere...kinda urban/Asian/modern. Our server greeted us quickly and continued to provide excellent service for our entire dinner. I regret I cannot remember her name...young, blonde gal...very friendly and efficient.

To the food: We started with a few things to share. 

Soft Shell Crab Kara Age: I love soft shell crab and this was excellent and well prepared. My friends enjoyed as well.

Tuna Tataki: I don't care for tuna, but this was actually quite good, nice presentation. My friends who like tuna really enjoyed this.

Tiger's Eyes: I don't care for salmon and didn't like this. My friends who do like salmon said it was not that good either. Nice presentation but not good tasting.

Godzilla: We all enjoyed this dish. Rather pricy for the portion though.

Bulgogi: My entrée...certainly unlike any bulgogi I've ever had. Rather greasy and bland. very small portion for the price.

Bibimbop: One of my friends' entrees...once again, not like any bibimbop I've ever had/seen. The egg on top was fried hard, should have been soft or even more traditional with a raw egg broken on top with the heat of the dish to 'cook' it. I didn't sample but my friend said it wasn't that good.

Udon: My other friend's entrée...I did not sample but she was not impressed.

Overall, would not choose to dine here again. Some things good, some things not so good or even bad. The fact that we had gift cards helped take the sting out of the rather pricy food. Also, it did seem to take a very long time for the entrée part of our meal to be served, especially when the place was practically empty.

data.title: Slow but Friendly Service, Nice Ambience, Average Food
data.text: This was the first time my family ate here; we chose to visit Sake Tumi because we like Korean BBQ and had high hopes.  Pros:  There's $3 validated parking at a nearby parking garage, we liked the minimalist decor and brick walls, and all the staff were friendly and helpful, particularly our server....really liked our server.  Also, I thought they had some interesting choices on the dessert menu.  Cons:  As stated in other reviews, this is not the place to come if you are in a hurry-service was slow.  Luckily we weren't in a rush to get anywhere after our visit so it didn't bother us.  The chicken teriyaki and kalbi were kind of bland, but we liked our appetizers and the bulgolgi.  I thought the various maki we ordered were tasty.  There are not a lot of options for Korean food in the Milwaukee area so we'll probably be back, but overall it wasn't the "Wow!" experience we were hoping for.  FYI:  If you go, be sure to check out the sea life murals in the bathrooms.

data.title: Horrible Service
data.text: My husband and I were seated at a table after repeatedly telling the host that we did not want to sit at the sushi bar. The server took 20 minutes to get to our table after being seated. Another 20 minute wait for our drinks and then a good 45 minute wait for our main course which was sushi. The place was not too busy so I was confused why the service was so bad. Will not return.

data.title: Great Service and Food
data.text: The server was very helpful in finding vegan and vegetarian options for my family. Thanks for accommodating us! I will definitely be back for a happy hour!

data.title: Good Food - Average Service
data.text: Food is always pretty good...service is hit or miss.  Our server was good, but it seemed like there were only two servers for a packed house.  She tried, but kitchen was behind and the speed of service was average.

data.title: Food good but Service really lacking
data.text: The service or lack of it really colored my opinion of this place. It was busy for a Wed night but the service was just off. Long wait time between drinks, appetizer and entrees. Drinks were left empty for about 15 minutes. It seemed like the staff would just disappear in the back. The calamari appetizer was excellent- lightly fried, great seasoning and aioli served with it was great. The King Kong roll was very good also. So the food was good but the experience not great.

data.title: Cute, Comfortable and Classy..... a good choice for sushi
data.text: 3 of us went for dinner at 630 on a Tuesday and the place was busy. the servers, while a little harried, answered all of our questions and suggested a couple things. Very knowledgeable. The food was good, the staff was friendly and the atmosphere was above reproach. PARKING is a night mare as is driving as several close places have valets that zip up and down the block (sometimes in reverse!) to take up any available parking.,

data.title: Great Sushi at a great price
data.text: Excellent value and quality a must try in Milwaukee! Small dining area but with a small sushi bar but really great location.

data.title: Great Asian Fusion in Milwaukee
data.text: We tried this on a whim and found the food to be reasonably priced and the menu had great variety.  Portions are generous, so if you're eying a couple of appetizers, plan on taking some of your dinner home.  Service was great, not excellent. A great option in what can be a very expensive downtown area.

data.title: Servie & Ambiance Lacking
data.text: We (2) arrived at our reservation time of 6:45 for a Groupon dinner & comedy show (which is just one Sat. night a month)  and were ready to order within 5 minutes of being seated. There was no wait and there were some empty tables. I cannot eat spicy at all and ordered the "Hawaiian" after assurance it was not spicy. Eating leftovers for lunch at work, I took a bite that was very green and avocado-y looking but turned out to be a tad of avocado disguising a teaspoon of horseradish. It was just like an old cartoon, I thought my head was going to explode with steam blowing out my ears! For 4 full minutes! Embarassing! Again, I cannot do spicy is any way, shape or form. Our 2 entrees were served at 7:42 and 7:47 despite staff knowing we were there for 8:00 show. Noticed couple next to us that were seated after us were eating their entrees well before we got ours. No time to enjoy. Staff unconcerned as we could see time was becoming tight. We took take home boxes. The Crab Ragoon appetizer was delicious, the pork Gyoza dumplings were good, the Sesame Chicken was very good and the Hawaiian (white fish and rice dish) was pretty good exceopt for that nasty horseradish surprise bite. Comedy show acoustics were awful. When the mic/mike was used, the sound was muffled and we could not hear. Fortunately the mic started working sporadically and then finally not at all & was ultimately abandoned and we could hear Ok for the most part but the comedians weren't very funny. The routine seemed very amateur. Seating had no chairbacks and our bad backs hated the lack of support. Seating was also in poor formation for viewing a comedy show. We had to sit uncomfortably and look sideways, some had to turn all the way around as they were grouped into squares for visiting with friends. Hallway stench smelled like sewer backup but staff did not acknowledge it either time as they led us to our table or room for the show. Spouse honestly wondered if this was a health department violation and if we were at risk. Staff did not appear to care if we were there or not.

data.title: Decent sushi
data.text: I was staying at Pfister hotel right by the restaurant, so I walked over here to eat.  the restaurant was small but it was nice.  Sushi was decent.

data.title: Great Lunch!
data.text: I met my boss in Milwaukee for a meeting.  It was lunch time after the meeting and he asked if I liked sushi.  He said that Saki Tumi was his favorite sushi restaurant. We arrived just after noon and were seated right away.  The service and food were both excellent!  I will be back next time I'm in town!
